RESUME
Cette tude examine la participation des populations durant la conception et
la mise en uvre du Programme dappui aux filires agro-sylvo-pastorale (PAFASP)
dans la Rgion du Centre-Nord du Burkina Faso. Compare aux exigences des outils
et mthodes participatives de gestion des projets et programmes de dveloppement,
il ressort que la participation des populations reste insuffisante. La phase de
conception a tenu compte dun nombre restreint de participants du secteur public, du
secteur priv et de la socit civile. Pendant la phase de mise en uvre, les
conditions doctroi des micro-projets ne sont pas toujours la porte de certaines
catgories dites pauvres. Or, lobjectif est de rduire la pauvret. Les conclusions de
la recherche nous ont conduits formuler des recommandations afin que les projets
ou programmes futurs ne tombent dans les mmes erreurs.

SUMMARY
This survey examines the involvement of the populations during the
conception and the setting in work of the support Program to the agro-sylvo-pastoral
paths (PAFASP) in the Region of the Centre-Nord of Burkina. Compared to the
requirements of the tools and methods participatifs of management of the projects
and programs of development, he/it comes out again that the involvement of the
populations insufficient rest. He phase of conception took into account a number
restricts participants of the public sector, the private sector and the civil society.
During the phase of setting in work, the conditions of concession of the micro-
projects are not always accessible to some categories say poor. However, the
objective is to reduce poverty. The findings of research drove us to formulate some
recommendations so that the projects or future programs don't fall in the same
mistakes.
